        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36451",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I do not see any problem, see the attached file test.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ramon",
                        "name": "ramon",
                        "displayName": "Ramon Henrique Ornelas",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T02:25:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T02:25:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36463",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tdm",
                        "name": "tdm",
                        "displayName": "Patrick van Dissel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I tried your test.php file and that does result in two exactly the same array outputs.\r\n\r\nBut via the Currency class in the toCurrency() function, with the following arrays:\r\nCurrent currency options:\r\n{code}\r\nArray ( [position] => 8 [script] => [format] => [display] => 2 [precision] => 2 [name] => Euro [currency] => EUR [symbol] => \u20ac ) \r\n{code}\r\n\r\nOptions given with th toCurrency() function:\r\n{code}\r\nArray ( [symbol] => Sk [precision] => 4 )\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nUsing the + way I get the following array back:\r\n{code}\r\nArray ( [position] => 8 [script] => [format] => [display] => 2 [precision] => 2 [name] => Euro [currency] => EUR [symbol] => \u20ac )\r\n{code}\r\n(so that's not merged)\r\n\r\nUsing the array_merge way I get the following array back:\r\n{code}\r\nArray ( [position] => 8 [script] => [format] => [display] => 2 [precision] => 4 [name] => Euro [currency] => EUR [symbol] => Sk )\r\n{code}\r\n(so that's correctly merged)\r\n\r\nEven the PHP Manual says the + way only appends data, so.. :)\r\n\r\nThanks",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tdm",
                        "name": "tdm",
                        "displayName": "Patrick van Dissel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T07:29:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T07:29:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36465",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The manual states:\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nThe + operator appends elements of remaining keys from the right handed array to the left handed, whereas duplicated keys are NOT overwritten.\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nWhich means that the default settings are only appended when you did not give them.\r\n\r\nYour example is not reproducable.\r\nNote that when you for example set a different display at initiation it could be that symbol is not used for this locale. This depends on your settings but is not reproducable with the data you gave.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T07:33:13.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T07:33:13.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36466",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Using your example and the options you gave I see no problem at all:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n$currency = new Zend_Currency();\r\n\r\nvar_dump($currency->toCurrency(200));\r\n\r\n$currencyOptions = array(\r\n    'symbol'        => 'Sk'\r\n    , 'precision'   => 4\r\n);\r\nvar_dump($currency->toCurrency(200, $currencyOptions));\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe returned output is:\r\n{code}\r\nstring '\u20ac 200,00' (length=11)\r\nstring 'Sk 200,0000' (length=12)\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThis is expected and correct behaviour.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T07:45:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T07:45:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36467",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Closing as not reproducable.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-24T07:46:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-24T07:46:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36497",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tdm",
                        "name": "tdm",
                        "displayName": "Patrick van Dissel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Is there a reason to use the + operand instead of the array_merge function?\r\nIf there's no real reason, isn't it then possible to just use the array_merge?\r\n\r\nBecause I really have the described problem when the + operand is used. I fixed it in my local copy of the Zend library by using the array_merge function instead of the + operand and now it works perfectly.\r\n\r\nIt's really strains, I can't reproduce it when using a simple test script but within my whole project it really is an issue.\r\nI'll try some more to find a way to reproduce it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tdm",
                        "name": "tdm",
                        "displayName": "Patrick van Dissel",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-25T04:33:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-25T04:33:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36509",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There are 2 reasons:\r\n\r\n* array_merge does not properly handle numeric keys\r\n* + is much better performant than array_merge\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-25T12:18:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-25T12:18:26.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
